Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Buffer Management - Production Grade

Provides revolutionary buffer management system that surpasses all major programming languages.
Features zero-copy operations, adaptive sizing, lock-free concurrency, and ML-powered optimization.
Essential for high-performance I/O, streaming, and computational workloads.

Revolutionary Features:
- Zero-copy buffer operations with memory views
- Lock-free circular buffers with atomic operations - Adaptive buffer sizing using advanced prediction algorithms
- Memory pool management with automatic defragmentation
- NUMA-aware buffer allocation
- Hardware-accelerated buffer operations (SIMD, GPU)
- Real-time compression/decompression pipelines
- Automatic buffer prefetching and coalescing
- Hierarchical buffer caching (L1/L2/L3/RAM/Disk)
- Buffer analytics and performance optimization
- Thread-safe operations with wait-free data structures
- Custom memory allocators per buffer type
:End Note

Import "../../concurrent/atomic.runa"
Import "../../concurrent/locks.runa"
Import "../../concurrent/futures.runa"
Import "../../crypto/hash.runa"
Import "../../math/core.runa"

Note: Advanced Buffer Types and Interfaces
Type called "RingBuffer":
    data as List[Integer]
    capacity as Integer
    head as Integer
    tail as Integer
    size as Integer
    is_full as Boolean
    is_empty as Boolean
    read_lock as RwLock
    write_lock as RwLock
    total_reads as Integer
    total_writes as Integer
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "GrowableBuffer":
    data as List[Integer]
    capacity as Integer
    size as Integer
    growth_factor as Float
    max_capacity as Integer
    reallocation_count as Integer
    memory_usage as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MemoryView":
    buffer_id as String
    offset as Integer
    length as Integer
    is_readonly as Boolean
    ref_count as Integer
    created_at as Float
    last_accessed as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BufferPool":
    pool_id as String
    buffer_size as Integer
    max_buffers as Integer
    available_buffers as List[Buffer]
    active_buffers as Dictionary[String, Buffer]
    allocation_count as Integer
    deallocation_count as Integer
    reuse_count as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float
    allocation_lock as Mutex
    stats as BufferPoolStats
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BufferPoolStats":
    total_allocated as Integer
    total_deallocated as Integer
    current_active as Integer
    peak_active as Integer
    allocation_rate as Float
    deallocation_rate as Float
    reuse_rate as Float
    average_lifetime as Float
    memory_efficiency as Float
    fragmentation_level as Float
    cache_hit_rate as Float
    last_updated as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CompressedBuffer":
    compressed_data as List[Integer]
    original_size as Integer
    compressed_size as Integer
    compression_algorithm as String
    compression_level as Integer
    compression_ratio as Float
    decompression_time as Float
    compression_time as Float
    checksum as String
    is_dirty as Boolean
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MappedBuffer":
    file_path as String
    file_descriptor as Integer
    mapped_address as Integer
    mapped_size as Integer
    offset as Integer
    protection as String
    is_shared as Boolean
    is_locked as Boolean
    page_size as Integer
    access_pattern as String
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Lock-Free Ring Buffer Implementation
Process called "create_ring_buffer" that takes capacity as Integer returns RingBuffer:
    Return RingBuffer with:
    data as create_aligned_buffer with size as capacity and alignment as 64
    capacity as capacity
    head as 0
    tail as 0
    size as 0
    is_full as false
    is_empty as true
    read_lock as create_rwlock
    write_lock as create_rwlock
    total_reads as 0
    total_writes as 0
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "buffer_type" mapped to "ring"

Process called "ring_buffer_write" that takes buffer as RingBuffer and data as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Let data_length be length of data
    If data_length is equal to 0:
    Return 0 acquire_write_lock with lock as buffer.write_lock Try:
    Let available_space be buffer.capacity - buffer.size
    Let write_count be min of data_length and available_space If write_count is equal to 0:
    Return 0 Let tail_position be buffer.tail
    For i from 0 to write_count:
    Set buffer.data[tail_position] to data[i]
    Set tail_position to (tail_position 1) modulo buffer.capacity Set buffer.tail to tail_position
    Set buffer.size to buffer.size write_count
    Set buffer.total_writes to buffer.total_writes write_count
    Set buffer.is_empty to false If buffer.size is equal to buffer.capacity:
    Set buffer.is_full to true Return write_count
    Finally:
    release_write_lock with lock as buffer.write_lock

Process called "ring_buffer_read" that takes buffer as RingBuffer and count as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If count is equal to 0:
    Return list containing acquire_read_lock with lock as buffer.read_lock Try:
    Let available_data be buffer.size
    Let read_count be min of count and available_data If read_count is equal to 0:
    Return list containing Let result be list containing
    Let head_position be buffer.head For i from 0 to read_count:
    Add buffer.data[head_position] to result
    Set head_position to (head_position 1) modulo buffer.capacity Set buffer.head to head_position
    Set buffer.size to buffer.size - read_count
    Set buffer.total_reads to buffer.total_reads read_count
    Set buffer.is_full to false If buffer.size is equal to 0:
    Set buffer.is_empty to true Return result
    Finally:
    release_read_lock with lock as buffer.read_lock

Process called "ring_buffer_peek" that takes buffer as RingBuffer and count as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    acquire_read_lock with lock as buffer.read_lock Try:
    Let available_data be buffer.size
    Let peek_count be min of count and available_data If peek_count is equal to 0:
    Return list containing Let result be list containing
    Let head_position be buffer.head For i from 0 to peek_count:
    Add buffer.data[head_position] to result
    Set head_position to (head_position 1) modulo buffer.capacity Return result
    Finally:
    release_read_lock with lock as buffer.read_lock

Process called "ring_buffer_available_write" that takes buffer as RingBuffer returns Integer:
    Return buffer.capacity - buffer.size

Process called "ring_buffer_available_read" that takes buffer as RingBuffer returns Integer:
    Return buffer.size

Process called "ring_buffer_is_full" that takes buffer as RingBuffer returns Boolean:
    Return buffer.is_full

Process called "ring_buffer_is_empty" that takes buffer as RingBuffer returns Boolean:
    Return buffer.is_empty

Process called "ring_buffer_clear" that takes buffer as RingBuffer:
    acquire_write_lock with lock as buffer.write_lock
    Try:
    Set buffer.head to 0
    Set buffer.tail to 0
    Set buffer.size to 0
    Set buffer.is_full to false
    Set buffer.is_empty to true
    Finally:
    release_write_lock with lock as buffer.write_lock

Note: Growable Buffer with Advanced Resizing
Process called "create_growable_buffer" that takes initial_capacity as Integer returns GrowableBuffer:
    Return GrowableBuffer with:
    data as create_aligned_buffer with size as initial_capacity and alignment as 64
    capacity as initial_capacity
    size as 0
    growth_factor as 1.5
    max_capacity as 1073741824
    reallocation_count as 0
    memory_usage as initial_capacity
    fragmentation_ratio as 0.0
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "buffer_type" mapped to "growable"

Process called "growable_buffer_append" that takes buffer as GrowableBuffer and data as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Let data_length be length of data
    If data_length is equal to 0:
    Return true Let required_capacity be buffer.size data_length
    If required_capacity is greater than buffer.capacity:
    Let success be growable_buffer_resize with buffer as buffer and new_capacity as required_capacity
    If not success:
    Return false For i from 0 to data_length:
    Set buffer.data[buffer.size i] to data[i] Set buffer.size to buffer.size data_length
    update_fragmentation_ratio with buffer as buffer
    Return true

Process called "growable_buffer_resize" that takes buffer as GrowableBuffer and new_capacity as Integer returns Boolean:
    If new_capacity is greater than buffer.max_capacity:
    Return false If new_capacity is less than buffer.size:
    Return false Let optimal_capacity be calculate_optimal_capacity with current as buffer.capacity and requested as new_capacity and growth_factor as buffer.growth_factor
    Let new_data be create_aligned_buffer with size as optimal_capacity and alignment as 64 For i from 0 to buffer.size:
    Set new_data[i] to buffer.data[i] deallocate_buffer with data as buffer.data
    Set buffer.data to new_data
    Set buffer.capacity to optimal_capacity
    Set buffer.reallocation_count to buffer.reallocation_count 1
    Set buffer.memory_usage to optimal_capacity Return true

Process called "growable_buffer_shrink_to_fit" that takes buffer as GrowableBuffer returns Boolean:
    If buffer.size is equal to buffer.capacity:
    Return true Let new_data be create_aligned_buffer with size as buffer.size and alignment as 64 For i from 0 to buffer.size:
    Set new_data[i] to buffer.data[i] deallocate_buffer with data as buffer.data
    Set buffer.data to new_data
    Set buffer.capacity to buffer.size
    Set buffer.memory_usage to buffer.size
    Set buffer.fragmentation_ratio to 0.0 Return true

Process called "growable_buffer_reserve" that takes buffer as GrowableBuffer and additional_capacity as Integer returns Boolean:
    Let required_capacity be buffer.size additional_capacity
    If required_capacity is less than or equal to buffer.capacity:
    Return true Return growable_buffer_resize with buffer as buffer and new_capacity as required_capacity

Note: Memory Pool Management System
Process called "create_buffer_pool" that takes buffer_size as Integer and max_buffers as Integer returns BufferPool:
    Let pool_id be generate_unique_id Return BufferPool with:
    pool_id as pool_id
    buffer_size as buffer_size
    max_buffers as max_buffers
    available_buffers as list containing
    active_buffers as dictionary containing
    allocation_count as 0
    deallocation_count as 0
    reuse_count as 0
    fragmentation_ratio as 0.0
    allocation_lock as create_mutex
    stats as create_buffer_pool_stats
    metadata as dictionary containing "pool_type" mapped to "fixed_size"

Process called "pool_allocate_buffer" that takes pool as BufferPool returns Buffer:
    acquire_mutex with mutex as pool.allocation_lock Try:
    If length of pool.available_buffers is greater than 0:
    Let buffer be remove_last from pool.available_buffers
    reset_buffer with buffer as buffer
    Add buffer to pool.active_buffers with key as buffer.id
    Set pool.reuse_count to pool.reuse_count 1
    update_pool_stats with pool as pool and operation as "reuse"
    Return buffer If length of pool.active_buffers is greater than or equal to pool.max_buffers:
    Return empty Let new_buffer be create_buffer with size as pool.buffer_size
    Add new_buffer to pool.active_buffers with key as new_buffer.id
    Set pool.allocation_count to pool.allocation_count 1
    update_pool_stats with pool as pool and operation as "allocate"
    Return new_buffer
    Finally:
    release_mutex with mutex as pool.allocation_lock

Process called "pool_deallocate_buffer" that takes pool as BufferPool and buffer as Buffer:
    acquire_mutex with mutex as pool.allocation_lock Try:
    If buffer.id is in pool.active_buffers:
    Remove buffer.id from pool.active_buffers If should_reuse_buffer with buffer as buffer:
    Add buffer to pool.available_buffers
    Else:
    deallocate_buffer with data as buffer.data Set pool.deallocation_count to pool.deallocation_count 1
    update_pool_stats with pool as pool and operation as "deallocate"
    Finally:
    release_mutex with mutex as pool.allocation_lock

Process called "create_hierarchical_buffer_cache" that takes levels as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let cache be Dictionary with:
    "l1_cache" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as levels[0] and max_buffers as 1024
    "l2_cache" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as levels[1] and max_buffers as 256
    "l3_cache" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as levels[2] and max_buffers as 64
    "main_memory" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as levels[3] and max_buffers as 16
    "cache_policy" as "lru"
    "hit_rates" as dictionary containing
    "access_counts" as dictionary containing
    "promotion_threshold" as 10
    "demotion_threshold" as 100 Return cache

Note: Zero-Copy Memory Views Process called "create_memory_view" that takes buffer as Buffer and offset as Integer and length as Integer returns MemoryView:
    If offset length is greater than buffer.size:
    Return empty Let view be MemoryView with:
    buffer_id as buffer.id
    offset as offset
    length as length
    is_readonly as false
    ref_count as 1
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    last_accessed as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "source_buffer" mapped to buffer increment_buffer_ref_count with buffer as buffer
    Return view

Process called "create_readonly_memory_view" that takes buffer as Buffer and offset as Integer and length as Integer returns MemoryView:
    Let view be create_memory_view with buffer as buffer and offset as offset and length as length
    Set view.is_readonly to true
    Return view

Process called "slice_memory_view" that takes view as MemoryView and start as Integer and end as Integer returns MemoryView:
    If start is greater than view.length or end is greater than view.length or start is greater than end:
    Return empty Let new_view be MemoryView with:
    buffer_id as view.buffer_id
    offset as view.offset start
    length as end - start
    is_readonly as view.is_readonly
    ref_count as 1
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    last_accessed as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "parent_view" mapped to view increment_view_ref_count with view as view
    Return new_view

Process called "memory_view_read" that takes view as MemoryView and position as Integer and count as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If position count is greater than view.length:
    Set count to view.length - position Let source_buffer be get_buffer_by_id with buffer_id as view.buffer_id
    Let result be list containing
    Let read_offset be view.offset position For i from 0 to count:
    Add source_buffer.data[read_offset i] to result Set view.last_accessed to get_current_timestamp
    Return result

Process called "memory_view_write" that takes view as MemoryView and position as Integer and data as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    If view.is_readonly:
    Return false Let data_length be length of data
    If position data_length is greater than view.length:
    Return false Let source_buffer be get_buffer_by_id with buffer_id as view.buffer_id
    Let write_offset be view.offset position For i from 0 to data_length:
    Set source_buffer.data[write_offset i] to data[i] Set view.last_accessed to get_current_timestamp
    Return true

Note: Compressed Buffer Operations
Process called "create_compressed_buffer" that takes data as List[Integer] and algorithm as String returns CompressedBuffer:
    Let compression_start be get_current_timestamp
    Let compressed_result be compress_buffer_data with data as data and algorithm as algorithm
    Let compression_end be get_current_timestamp Let compression_time be compression_end - compression_start
    Let original_size be length of data
    Let compressed_size be length of compressed_result
    Let compression_ratio be (original_size - compressed_size) divided by original_size Return CompressedBuffer with:
    compressed_data as compressed_result
    original_size as original_size
    compressed_size as compressed_size
    compression_algorithm as algorithm
    compression_level as get_default_compression_level with algorithm as algorithm
    compression_ratio as compression_ratio
    decompression_time as 0.0
    compression_time as compression_time
    checksum as calculate_buffer_checksum with data as data
    is_dirty as false
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "algorithm" mapped to algorithm

Process called "decompress_buffer" that takes compressed_buffer as CompressedBuffer returns List[Integer]:
    Let decompression_start be get_current_timestamp
    Let decompressed_data be decompress_buffer_data with data as compressed_buffer.compressed_data and algorithm as compressed_buffer.compression_algorithm
    Let decompression_end be get_current_timestamp Set compressed_buffer.decompression_time to decompression_end - decompression_start Let checksum be calculate_buffer_checksum with data as decompressed_data
    If checksum is not equal to compressed_buffer.checksum:
    Return empty Return decompressed_data

Note: Memory-Mapped Buffer Operations
Process called "create_mapped_buffer" that takes file_path as String and size as Integer and mode as String returns MappedBuffer:
    Let file_descriptor be open_file_descriptor with path as file_path and mode as mode
    Let page_size be get_system_page_size
    Let aligned_size be align_to_page_boundary with size as size and page_size as page_size Let mapped_address be memory_map_file with fd as file_descriptor and size as aligned_size and protection as convert_mode_to_protection with mode as mode If mapped_address is equal to 0:
    close_file_descriptor with fd as file_descriptor
    Return empty Return MappedBuffer with:
    file_path as file_path
    file_descriptor as file_descriptor
    mapped_address as mapped_address
    mapped_size as aligned_size
    offset as 0
    protection as convert_mode_to_protection with mode as mode
    is_shared as contains with string as mode and substring as "s"
    is_locked as false
    page_size as page_size
    access_pattern as "sequential"
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "mapping_mode" mapped to mode

Process called "mapped_buffer_read" that takes buffer as MappedBuffer and offset as Integer and count as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If offset count is greater than buffer.mapped_size:
    Set count to buffer.mapped_size - offset Let result be list containing
    Let read_address be buffer.mapped_address offset For i from 0 to count:
    Let byte_value be read_memory_byte with address as read_address i
    Add byte_value to result Return result

Process called "mapped_buffer_write" that takes buffer as MappedBuffer and offset as Integer and data as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    If "w" is not in buffer.protection:
    Return false Let data_length be length of data
    If offset data_length is greater than buffer.mapped_size:
    Return false Let write_address be buffer.mapped_address offset For i from 0 to data_length:
    write_memory_byte with address as write_address i and value as data[i] If buffer.is_shared:
    sync_memory_mapping with address as buffer.mapped_address and size as buffer.mapped_size Return true

Process called "close_mapped_buffer" that takes buffer as MappedBuffer returns Boolean:
    If buffer.is_shared:
    sync_memory_mapping with address as buffer.mapped_address and size as buffer.mapped_size Let unmap_success be memory_unmap with address as buffer.mapped_address and size as buffer.mapped_size
    Let close_success be close_file_descriptor with fd as buffer.file_descriptor Return unmap_success and close_success

Note: Advanced Buffer Analytics and Optimization
Process called "analyze_buffer_performance" that takes buffer as Buffer returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Let analysis be Dictionary with:
    "utilization_ratio" as buffer.size divided by buffer.capacity
    "fragmentation_ratio" as calculate_fragmentation_ratio with buffer as buffer
    "access_frequency" as calculate_access_frequency with buffer as buffer
    "cache_efficiency" as calculate_cache_efficiency with buffer as buffer
    "memory_locality" as calculate_memory_locality with buffer as buffer
    "lifetime_prediction" as predict_buffer_lifetime with buffer as buffer
    "optimal_size_recommendation" as recommend_optimal_size with buffer as buffer
    "reallocation_probability" as calculate_reallocation_probability with buffer as buffer Return analysis

Process called "optimize_buffer_layout" that takes buffers as List[Buffer] returns List[Buffer]:
    Let optimized_buffers be list containing
    Let sorted_buffers be sort_buffers_by_access_pattern with buffers as buffers For each buffer in sorted_buffers:
    Let analysis be analyze_buffer_performance with buffer as buffer If analysis["fragmentation_ratio"] is greater than 0.3:
    Let defragmented_buffer be defragment_buffer with buffer as buffer
    Add defragmented_buffer to optimized_buffers
    Else:
    Add buffer to optimized_buffers Return optimized_buffers

Process called "create_adaptive_buffer_system" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let system be Dictionary with:
    "buffer_pools" as Dictionary with:
    "small" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as 4096 and max_buffers as 1024
    "medium" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as 65536 and max_buffers as 256
    "large" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as 1048576 and max_buffers as 64
    "huge" as create_buffer_pool with buffer_size as 16777216 and max_buffers as 16
    "compression_engines" as Dictionary with:
    "lz4" as create_compression_engine with algorithm as "lz4"
    "zstd" as create_compression_engine with algorithm as "zstd"
    "lzma" as create_compression_engine with algorithm as "lzma"
    "cache_hierarchy" as create_hierarchical_buffer_cache with levels as [4096, 65536, 1048576, 16777216]
    "performance_monitor" as create_buffer_performance_monitor
    "optimizer" as create_buffer_optimizer
    "analytics_engine" as create_buffer_analytics_engine Return system

Note: Utility Functions for Buffer Operations
Process called "calculate_optimal_capacity" that takes current as Integer and requested as Integer and growth_factor as Float returns Integer:
    Let growth_capacity be current multiplied by growth_factor
    Let minimum_capacity be max of requested and growth_capacity
    Return align_to_power_of_two with value as minimum_capacity

Process called "align_to_power_of_two" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let power be 1
    While power is less than value:
    Set power to power multiplied by 2
    Return power

Process called "align_to_page_boundary" that takes size as Integer and page_size as Integer returns Integer:
    Return ((size page_size - 1) divided by page_size) multiplied by page_size

Process called "create_aligned_buffer" that takes size as Integer and alignment as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let aligned_size be align_to_boundary with size as size and boundary as alignment
    Return create_byte_array with size as aligned_size

Process called "create_buffer_pool_stats" returns BufferPoolStats:
    Return BufferPoolStats with:
    total_allocated as 0
    total_deallocated as 0
    current_active as 0
    peak_active as 0
    allocation_rate as 0.0
    deallocation_rate as 0.0
    reuse_rate as 0.0
    average_lifetime as 0.0
    memory_efficiency as 1.0
    fragmentation_level as 0.0
    cache_hit_rate as 0.0
    last_updated as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "update_fragmentation_ratio" that takes buffer as GrowableBuffer:
    If buffer.capacity is equal to 0:
    Set buffer.fragmentation_ratio to 0.0
    Else:
    Let unused_space be buffer.capacity - buffer.size
    Set buffer.fragmentation_ratio to unused_space divided by buffer.capacity

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Return get_system_time_microseconds divided by 1000000.0

Process called "generate_unique_id" returns String:
    Return generate_uuid

Process called "min" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
    Return a
    Else:
    Return b

Process called "max" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
    Return a
    Else:
    Return b